undecided on whether to commit your way to Jehovah? Take note of the trust and

00:05:59.060 --> 00:06:05.019
confidence Brother Brown showed in dedicating his life to God. Be assured that

00:06:05.019 --> 00:06:10.620
Jehovah will guide and care for us if we give him the opportunity. Brother

00:06:10.620 --> 00:06:15.259
Brown now enjoys the blessing of living under Jehovah's protection, serving

00:06:15.259 --> 00:06:21.060
of the ministerial servant and regular pioneer. You too can experience Jehovah's

00:06:21.060 --> 00:06:26.899
spiritual protection as we'll learn throughout our program. The theme of our

00:06:26.899 --> 00:06:33.139
broadcast is a very comforting one, being securely wrapped in the bag of life

00:06:33.139 --> 00:06:38.819
with Jehovah. Perhaps the thought of being securely wrapped makes us think of a

00:06:38.819 --> 00:06:43.699
faithfully swaddled baby or being enveloped in the warm blanket on a cold

00:06:43.699 --> 00:06:49.339
night. In the Bible, these words were uttered by the woman Abigail to Jehovah

00:06:49.339 --> 00:06:54.180
servant David. To understand the meaning of the words and their importance

00:06:54.180 --> 00:07:01.019
today, let's review the context the first Samuel chapter 25. David and 600 of

00:07:01.019 --> 00:07:05.459
his men were dwelling as fugitives. They eventually encountered men who

00:07:05.459 --> 00:07:10.699
worked as shepherds for Abigail's husband, Navel. David and his men began to

00:07:10.699 --> 00:07:15.300
help guard Navel's flocks and serve as a protective wall for Navel's flocks

00:07:15.300 --> 00:07:21.220
and servants against thieves and invaders who roamed through the wilderness. It

00:07:21.220 --> 00:07:26.540
was likely challenging to find enough food for 600 soldiers. So David decided

00:07:26.540 --> 00:07:31.500
to send 10 of his men to kindly ask Navel for food in repayment for the

00:07:31.500 --> 00:07:40.060
services that they had performed. But at first Samuel chapter 25 verse 10 and 11

00:07:40.060 --> 00:07:48.879
note Navel's reply. Navel answered David's servants, who is David? And who is the

00:07:48.879 --> 00:07:53.540
son of Jesse? Nowadays, many servants are breaking away from their

00:07:53.540 --> 00:07:59.819
masters. Do I have to take my bread and my water and the meat that I butchered

00:07:59.819 --> 00:08:06.180
from my shears and give it to men who come from who knows where? This was not

00:08:06.180 --> 00:08:11.459
the response that David and his men were expecting to hear. The Bible describes

00:08:11.459 --> 00:08:17.300
Navel as a very harsh, worthless man. And this is certainly evidence by his

00:08:17.300 --> 00:08:23.379
reply. He screamed insults at the messengers and ridiculed David, comparing

00:08:23.379 --> 00:08:29.459
him to a runaway servant. So David decided to take matters into his own hands.

00:08:29.459 --> 00:08:37.379
And resolve the situation the way many people today might. By fighting. In verse 13,

00:08:37.379 --> 00:08:43.980
he has 400 of his men prepare themselves for battle with one mission to wipe out

00:08:43.980 --> 00:08:49.980
every male and Navel's household. Eventually, we're getting back to Abigail

00:08:49.980 --> 00:08:54.259
about what her husband had done. Without telling Navel, she gathered an

00:08:54.259 --> 00:08:58.580
abundance of food and went out to meet David. When she met up with him,

00:08:58.580 --> 00:09:03.899
she poured out her heart at length, asking David to forgive her personally and

00:09:03.899 --> 00:09:09.019
making a powerful plea for mercy on behalf of her husband and her household.

00:09:09.019 --> 00:09:14.940
She acknowledged that Navel was a foolish and senseless man. So she urged David

00:09:14.940 --> 00:09:19.539
not to take any action that might bring blood guilt upon him or cause him to be

00:09:19.539 --> 00:09:25.019
affected by a troubled conscience. As Abigail concluded her appeal to David,

00:09:25.019 --> 00:09:33.419
notice what she tells him in verse 29, the theme of our discussion. When

00:09:33.419 --> 00:09:39.500
someone rises up to pursue you and seeks your life, the life of my Lord will be

00:09:39.500 --> 00:09:44.820
wrapped securely in the bag of life with Jehovah your God. But the lives of

00:09:44.820 --> 00:09:51.330
your enemies, he will hurl away like stones from a sling, just as we might wrap

00:09:51.330 --> 00:09:56.090
up something valuable in order to protect and preserve it. Abigail was

00:09:56.090 --> 00:10:01.250
telling David that is how his life would be in Jehovah's hands. Jehovah would

00:10:01.250 --> 00:10:06.090
protect and preserve David's life from his enemies. As long as he did not seek

00:10:06.090 --> 00:10:12.169
to save himself by personal efforts, but waited on Jehovah, trusting in the one

00:10:12.169 --> 00:10:20.340
to whom he owed his life. What lessons can we learn from this account? As David

00:10:20.340 --> 00:10:25.779
saw, his relationship with Jehovah was a protection. In verse 32, he

00:10:25.779 --> 00:10:31.500
acknowledges that God has sent Abigail with the warning. We learn that Jehovah's

00:10:31.500 --> 00:10:36.659
spiritual protection for us is related to the quality of our relationship with

00:10:36.659 --> 00:10:45.259
him. That's why the Bible tells us at James chapter 4, verse 8, draw close to

00:10:45.259 --> 00:10:51.940
God and he will draw close to you. Jehovah invites us to draw near to him

00:10:51.940 --> 00:10:58.299
because he wants to receive us into his favor as his friends. When we dedicate

00:10:58.299 --> 00:11:03.139
our lives and vow to serve him unconditionally, we gain an approved standing

00:11:03.139 --> 00:11:08.820
with him, we're figuratively put in that bag of life. And as we work to develop a

00:11:08.820 --> 00:11:13.500
close personal relationship with him, then we can experience Jehovah's

00:11:13.500 --> 00:11:18.820
friendship and protection. We would never want to restrict Jehovah's protection

00:11:18.820 --> 00:11:25.340
by not looking to him for guidance or relying on our own thinking. Now, can we

00:11:25.340 --> 00:11:30.980
think of areas or situations that might require us to wait on Jehovah? Perhaps

00:11:30.980 --> 00:11:37.100
we're experiencing literal opposition at work or at school. Like Abigail, he

00:11:37.100 --> 00:11:41.500
might face the challenge of living with a difficult marriage made. Maybe we're

00:11:41.500 --> 00:11:47.460
battling a health issue and loyalty is needed regarding our medical choices. Or

00:11:47.460 --> 00:11:51.580
it may be that we live in a country where we cannot preach freely or we face

00:11:51.580 --> 00:11:58.419
opposition for our beliefs. Really, it could be any number of situations, but it is

00:11:58.419 --> 00:12:05.379
our response the way we handle the situation that indicates how much we are

00:12:05.379 --> 00:12:11.580
allowing Jehovah to help us. Do we trust him enough that we can leave the

00:12:11.580 --> 00:12:18.299
matter in his hands and see how he works things out in our behalf? We have to

00:12:18.299 --> 00:12:23.500
manifest Christian qualities in order to do that. Think about what qualities

00:12:23.500 --> 00:12:29.019
displayed by Abigail and David impress you most. Two, they come to mind are

00:12:29.019 --> 00:12:34.860
patience and reasonableness. Patience is closely connected with endurance and

00:12:34.860 --> 00:12:40.220
enables one to put up with difficult circumstances while maintaining a positive

00:12:40.220 --> 00:12:47.580
attitude. Reasonableness describes a person who is fair, considerate, willing to

00:12:47.580 --> 00:12:53.659
yield to others. How well this describes Abigail? It must have been quite a

00:12:53.659 --> 00:12:58.700
challenge to live with someone like Nebel. But nowhere do we read that she was

00:12:58.700 --> 00:13:03.940
ever disrespectful of him or that she belittled him. Even when she referred to

00:13:03.940 --> 00:13:09.220
him as senseless in verse 25, from Jehovah's standpoint, her comments were

00:13:09.220 --> 00:13:16.059
proper because Nebel's actions put his entire household in danger. How about

00:13:16.059 --> 00:13:21.580
David? He was in a position of authority, but he showed great patience and

00:13:21.580 --> 00:13:26.139
reasonableness in listening to Abigail and having the good sense to know that

00:13:26.139 --> 00:13:31.220
she was right. That's not always easy to do when the heat of the moment or when

00:13:31.220 --> 00:13:36.860
we're upset. Perhaps you recall that our don't give up regional convention

00:13:36.860 --> 00:13:42.940
last year. When discussing 2nd Peter chapter 1 verses 5 through 8, we learned a

00:13:42.940 --> 00:13:46.940
nice formula that can help us to cultivate and strengthen Christian

00:13:46.940 --> 00:13:55.299
qualities. We were encouraged to study them, meditate on them, and put them into

00:13:55.299 --> 00:14:00.220
practice. If we apply this formula with the qualities of patience and

00:14:00.220 --> 00:14:05.740
reasonableness, it can help us to endure our trials successfully. And we're

00:14:05.740 --> 00:14:10.779
confident that Jehovah will supply us with whatever power we need so that we

00:14:10.779 --> 00:14:18.340
will not tire out as we continue to endure and put our trust in him. In addition

00:14:18.340 --> 00:14:22.340
to developing these qualities, something else that can help us is our spiritual

00:14:22.340 --> 00:14:28.539
routine. Our consistent routine of study, meeting attendance, and the ministry

00:14:28.539 --> 00:14:36.220
will help us remain busy, stay active, and make good decisions. We'll have no

00:14:36.220 --> 00:14:42.539
time to become curious or occupy what the things this world has to offer. It's

00:14:42.539 --> 00:14:47.059
good to remember the people during the days of Haggai. When the Jews lost

00:14:47.059 --> 00:14:52.100
their focus and started neglecting Jehovah's Temple, they lost his

00:14:52.100 --> 00:14:58.899
blessing and protection spiritually. And what was the result? Well, notice

00:14:58.899 --> 00:15:04.580
how Haggai draws our attention to a different type of bag at Haggai chapter

00:15:04.580 --> 00:15:14.940
1 verse 6. You have so much seed, but you harvest little. You eat, but it is not

00:15:14.940 --> 00:15:21.700
to satisfaction. You drink, but you do not drink your fill. You put on clothing

00:15:22.259 --> 00:15:29.539
but no one gets warm. The one who hires himself out puts his wages in a bag full

00:15:29.539 --> 00:15:36.620
of holes. The Jews sowed seed but had a meager harvest. They lacked enough food

00:15:36.620 --> 00:15:41.740
to satisfy their needs. They were unable to clothe themselves with warm garments.

00:15:41.740 --> 00:15:48.179
Because Jehovah withheld his blessings, Haggai rightly compared them to a man

00:15:48.179 --> 00:15:54.620
who puts his wages in a bag full of holes. Imagine the disappointment of

00:15:54.620 --> 00:15:59.179
discovering that hard-earned wages had gradually disappeared through a leaking

00:15:59.179 --> 00:16:05.899
bag. Of course, our focus is not material prosperity because whether we have

00:16:05.899 --> 00:16:10.899
an abundance of material things or not, if we fail to receive Jehovah's

00:16:10.899 --> 00:16:19.139
blessing, our spirituality is jeopardized. So we must be determined to never lose

00:16:19.139 --> 00:16:26.059
our focus and keep Jehovah in the forefront of our lives. When we examine the

00:16:26.059 --> 00:16:31.700
life of David, it's evident that he enjoyed a preserved and protected

00:16:31.700 --> 00:16:38.259
relationship with God. When we read the book of Psalms, take note of how David

00:16:38.299 --> 00:16:46.299
describes Jehovah's protective care. In Psalm 18, Psalm 31, and Psalm 34, as he

00:16:46.299 --> 00:16:53.139
went through distresses, just beautiful accounts. Now, did David always do

00:16:53.139 --> 00:16:59.460
everything the right way? No. Think of his encounter with naval. While his

00:16:59.460 --> 00:17:06.619
angry reaction was understandable, his way of expressing it was not correct. But

00:17:06.619 --> 00:17:11.660
David learned from his mistakes and each new trial that he went through

00:17:11.660 --> 00:17:18.180
strengthened his relationship with Jehovah even more. For example, after the

00:17:18.180 --> 00:17:23.859
ordeal with naval, a short time later, David married Abigail. They were still

00:17:23.859 --> 00:17:29.099
fugitives, but he found a king that befriended them and gave David's men and

00:17:29.099 --> 00:17:35.579
family a land to dwell in. One day, while all the men were away, the amalachites

00:17:35.579 --> 00:17:41.259
raided and burned the city and carried off all the men's wives, children, and

00:17:41.259 --> 00:17:48.140
flocks. Upon returning and seeing what had happened, David and his men wept.

00:17:48.140 --> 00:17:55.099
Grief quickly turned to bitterness, and David's men spoke of stoning him. This

00:17:55.099 --> 00:17:59.900
was likely quite stressful for David. He was concerned for the safety of his

00:17:59.900 --> 00:18:05.500
family, and likely he was frustrated that his men had turned on him. Maybe

00:18:05.500 --> 00:18:11.460
he felt disrespected again as he had with naval. So how would he handle this

00:18:11.460 --> 00:18:19.980
situation? We get a glimpse of David's feelings at 1 Samuel, chapter 30, verse 6.

00:18:19.980 --> 00:18:28.099
David was very distressed because the men were talking of stoning him, for all

00:18:28.099 --> 00:18:33.779
the men had become very bitter over the loss of their sons and daughters. But

00:18:33.859 --> 00:18:42.740
notice how did David handle the situation? The verse continues, but David

00:18:42.740 --> 00:18:52.660
strengthened himself by Jehovah his God. How did he do this? Verse 8 says, David

00:18:52.660 --> 00:19:00.019
inquired of Jehovah. This time, David has a different thought process and

00:19:00.019 --> 00:19:07.619
response. Immediately, he remembers to consult Jehovah. Isn't this a nice

00:19:07.619 --> 00:19:11.859
reminder that when you and I are going through difficult trials and situations,

00:19:12.579 --> 00:19:18.259
we want to immediately pray to Jehovah and seek his direction through the pages of

00:19:18.259 --> 00:19:24.019
his word, the Bible. This is essential for our spiritual protection.

00:19:24.900 --> 00:19:31.859
So in review, as we face difficult situations in life, may we look for

00:19:31.859 --> 00:19:37.140
opportunities to show and develop our Christian qualities, such as patience and

00:19:37.140 --> 00:19:42.980
reasonableness. These qualities show Jehovah that we want to be like him, that we

00:19:42.980 --> 00:19:47.700
have the mental disposition of Christ, and that we will allow him to guide us

00:19:48.019 --> 00:19:55.380
constantly. Next, may we keep focused and busy in the work of the Lord. By drawing

00:19:55.380 --> 00:20:01.619
close to Jehovah through prayer and engaging in spiritual activities, we make the best of

00:20:01.619 --> 00:20:08.420
our situation now. But we will also find everlasting protection in Jehovah's hands,

00:20:09.220 --> 00:20:18.309
safely swaddled, and securely wrapped in his bag of life. We need to rely on Jehovah's

00:20:18.390 --> 00:20:24.950
guidance even in the most severe trials. It's possible that you may face a life-threatening issue

00:20:24.950 --> 00:20:31.509
where there's no desirable option, but a decision is necessary. In the following

00:20:31.509 --> 00:20:39.430
dramatization, Emma is faced with a situation like this. What will she do? And how will God's

00:20:39.430 --> 00:20:48.569
word help her to make a decision? When Thomas and I first learned I was pregnant,

00:20:48.569 --> 00:21:03.990
we were both really shocked. But then we grew more and more excited. And we were so thrilled

00:21:03.990 --> 00:21:14.569
when we saw our little girl for the first time. We really didn't care if it was a boy or a girl.

00:21:15.369 --> 00:21:36.619
We just wanted the baby to be healthy. Unfortunately, our hopes were completely destroyed when the

00:21:36.619 --> 00:21:42.619
doctor told us that the baby would likely be born with severe problems and could even die.

00:21:52.220 --> 00:21:57.339
My husband and his parents are not Jehovah's witnesses, but they do feel abortion is wrong.

00:22:06.380 --> 00:22:15.000
Still, they thought that we should listen to our doctor's advice. I couldn't believe this was

00:22:15.000 --> 00:22:21.960
happening. I even questioned why Jehovah would allow it. I really felt it was more than I could

00:22:21.960 --> 00:22:31.210
bear. Thomas asked me what I wanted to do, and I told him that I could never have an abortion.

00:22:32.089 --> 00:22:38.009
He agreed that normally it would be wrong, but felt that in our situation God would understand

00:22:42.869 --> 00:22:48.390
I was so overwhelmed. I was being pressured to make a decision I knew was wrong,

00:22:48.950 --> 00:22:57.589
but that everyone was telling me was based on my child. I had never felt so alone.

00:23:00.519 --> 00:23:16.900
I needed Jehovah more than ever, so I poured out my heart to him in prayer. And then I did

00:23:16.900 --> 00:23:57.829
research. I showed Thomas the scripture I had found. If men should struggle with each other

00:23:57.829 --> 00:24:07.259
and they hurt a pregnant woman, if a fatality does occur, then you must give life for life.

00:24:08.619 --> 00:24:14.700
Jehovah views even the unintentional killing of an unborn child as a serious sin.

00:24:14.700 --> 00:24:26.740
So how could we intentionally take the life of our child? I made my decision clear to our doctor.

00:24:30.579 --> 00:24:34.099
Thank you. I'll have a look at that later. And to my in-laws.

00:24:37.640 --> 00:24:43.559
There was a chance the diagnosis was incorrect, and I'd love to say that that's what occurred.

00:24:44.440 --> 00:24:49.799
But it did not. My daughter Chloe only loved a few weeks after she was born,

00:24:50.519 --> 00:24:56.519
and losing her was the hardest thing I've ever had to endure. But Jehovah gave me the courage

00:24:56.519 --> 00:25:03.160
to explain my beliefs to my husband, my in-laws, and the medical staff, and they all expressed

